# CRITICAL: Road-routing configuration for verified fare calculation
# ================================================================
#
# Official commuter fares should come from verified road routes.
# The planner now tries OpenRouteService first and Google Routes second.
#
# Without proper road-based routing:
# - San Antonio to Basiao: GPS = 7.6km, Reality = 21km
# - This would undercharge drivers by ₱40+ per trip!
# - Drivers and operators would lose significant income
#
# Setup Instructions:
# ===================
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing project
# 3. Enable the following APIs:
#    - Routes API (REQUIRED for routing fallback)
#    - Geocoding API (required if you use server-side geocoding)
#    - Maps JavaScript API (optional, for map visualization)
# 4. Create API credentials (API Key)
# 5. Copy this file to .env.local and add your keys below:

# Shared server-side key for Google Maps web services (geocoding, optional)
GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_API_KEY=your_google_maps_server_api_key_here

# Dedicated server-side key for Google Routes fallback (recommended)
# Do not restrict this key by HTTP referrer because planner routing happens server-side.
GOOGLE_ROUTES_API_KEY=your_google_routes_server_api_key_here

# Alternative (if you prefer client-side key):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

# API Key Security (Important):
# ============================
# - Restrict browser keys by HTTP referrer only for client-side maps
# - Restrict server keys by API usage, and by IP only if you control fixed egress IPs
# - Do not use HTTP referrer restrictions on GOOGLE_ROUTES_API_KEY
# - Monitor usage to avoid unexpected charges
# - Set usage quotas/limits in Google Cloud Console

# Other Configuration (Optional):
# ===============================
# DATABASE_URL=your_database_url_here
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your_nextauth_secret_here
# NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_SESSION_MAX_AGE_SECONDS=28800
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MS=7200000
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_REVALIDATION_MS=60000
# ROUTING_ORS_TIMEOUT_MS=3500
# ROUTING_GOOGLE_ROUTES_TIMEOUT_MS=3500

# After adding your API key:
# =========================
# 1. Save this file as .env.local (remove .example)
# 2. Restart your development server: npm run dev
# 3. Test route calculation to ensure it works
# 4. If ORS fails, confirm the planner returns provider "google_routes"
# 5. Verify distances match real-world road distances
